==English==

===Etymology===
From [[Ancient Greek]] [[Έλλην]] (''Ellen'') "Greek", "luminary", from prefix [[έλ-]] (''el'') "sun, bright, shiny". (See [[helios]] "sun", [[electron]] "amber", etc.). In Greek mythology [[Έλλην]], whom the [[Έλληνες]] (''Hellenes'') "Greeks" were named after, 
was the son of [[Δευκαλίων]] (''Deucalion'') and [[Πύρρα]] (''Pyrra'').

===Noun===
#An inhabitant, resident, or a person of descent from [[Hellas]], "Greece".
#Another word for [[Hellene]].

